Lake Worth is a city in

Palm Beach International Airport.
Tri-Rail has rail service to/from west palm beach all the way down to miami.
Cabs are readily available at taxi stops around the city.  PalmTran has local bus service to destinations around the county.

Lake Worth beach has a pier with picnic tables and a restaurant.  There are also shops and a public pool right near the beach.  The beach has plenty of parking, and is usually very busy on the weekends.

Downtown Lake Worth has a new-agey kind of feel, with ample yoga studios, antique shops, and local fashion stores.  Enjoy a stroll around the downtown area.  The First and third Fridays of each month see the streets closed off with live music and temporary shops set up.  Every Thursday night is biker night so motorcyclists feel welcome downtown.
Surf shops, a news stand, antique shops, smoothie/natural food store, ice cream, starbucks, all are in the downtown area.
Italian, Greek, Pub food, Pizza, the "Taco Lady" Mexican Restaurant, Thai, Sushi - all are available in and around the few block radius of downtown lake worth.

value: content=Is a very old and yet classy restaurant located on the Lake Worth Pier. Good for breakfast.

Plenty of bars in the downtown area. Sneaker's on dixie highway is open until 5AM on weekends.
Four Seasons resort is on the intracoastal.  If that's out of your price range, a short drive up and down dixie will provide you with a plethora of cheap motel choices.
If you are walking late at night, do not stray far from the downtown area. Lake Worth is notorious for its gang problem.
